org.openbel.framework.api
Interface PathFinder

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractPathFinder, BasicPathFinder
public interface PathFinder

PathFinder defines a utility to find paths within a Kam. The path finder must implement:

  • Find all paths from source set to a target set
  • Scan outwards from a source set
  • Interconnect between nodes in a source set

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

Method Detail

findPaths

SimplePath[] findPaths(Kam.KamNode source,
                       Kam.KamNode target)
Finds all paths, if there are any, between the source and target Kam.KamNode.

Parameters:
source - Kam.KamNode, the source KAM node to search from, which cannot be null
target - Kam.KamNode, the target KAM node to search to, which cannot be null
Returns:
a populated KamPath[], or an empty array if no paths were found
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if source or target is null, or if they do not exist within the Kam to traverse

findPaths

SimplePath[] findPaths(Kam.KamNode[] sources,
                       Kam.KamNode[] targets)
Finds all paths, if there are any, between all pairs of Kam.KamNode sources and targets.

Parameters:
sources - KamNode[], array of source KAM nodes to search from, which cannot be null or empty
targets - KamNode[], array of target KAM nodes to search to, which cannot be null or empty
Returns:
a populated KamPath[], or an empty array if no paths were found
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if sources or targets is null, empty, or if any Kam.KamNode does not exist within the Kam to traverse

interconnect

SimplePath[] interconnect(Kam.KamNode[] sources)
Finds all paths, if there are any, that interconnect any pair of nodes.

Parameters:
nodes - KamNode[], array of KAM nodes to interconnect, which cannot be null and must contain at least two KAM nodes
Returns:
a populated KamPath[], or an empty array if no paths were found
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if sources is null or does not contain at least two KAM nodes, or if any KAM node does not exist within the Kam to traverse

scan

SimplePath[] scan(Kam.KamNode source)
Finds all paths, if there are any, that scan out from the source Kam.KamNode.

The implementation of the scan algorithm should impose path constraints in order to prevent infinite graph traversal.

Parameters:
source - Kam.KamNode, the source KAM node to scan out from, which cannot be null
Returns:
a populated KamPath[], or an empty array if no paths were found
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if source is null, or if source does not exist within the Kam to traverse

scan

SimplePath[] scan(Kam.KamNode[] sources)
Finds all paths, if there are any, that scan out from the Kam.KamNode sources.

The implementation of the scan algorithm should impose constraints in order to prevent infinite graph traversal.

Parameters:
sources - KamNode[], array of source KAM nodes to scan out from, which cannot be null or empty
Returns:
a populated KamPath[], or an empty array if no paths were found
Throws:
InvalidArgument - Thrown if sources is null, empty, or if any Kam.KamNode does not exist within the Kam to traverse
